<subSubSection box="[312,1226,484,510]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1324,444,830]" box="[312,1226,484,510]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">DISTRIBUTION. Cosmopolitan, but only under cover in cooler temperate areas.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1324,444,830]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
HOST PLANTS. Filicopsida ­ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.B. Presl" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="R. Brown" box="[675,858,524,550]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Gleicheniaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhardi" authorityYear="1805" box="[879,1043,524,549]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Dicranopteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[879,1043,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Dicranopteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
? 
<emphasis box="[1072,1162,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">linearis</emphasis>
; also highly polyphagous on Angiospermae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1324,444,830]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
COMMENTS. We ae only aware of a single record of this major pest species­group from a fern, and it concerns just two puparial specimens collected in the Genting Highlands, peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[394,502,684,710]" name="Malaysia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(BMNH), on a fern species that rapidly colonises newly cleared land in the tropics. The vasiform orifice is a little broader than is typical for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gennadius" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1118,1225,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Bemisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tabaci">
<emphasis box="[1118,1225,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. tabaci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the geminate pore/porette distribution and stout caudal setae indicate inclusion in this important species­group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
